(Very minor) but I can't make JIRA say that...

Array.fill(-1)("Foo") returns a 0-length Array. It should probably throw an exception, like new Array:
```scala
scala> new Array[Int](-1)
java.lang.NegativeArraySizeException
	at .<init>(<console>:8)
